{
  "stem": "5758.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We had chamber music and Viennese waltzes, and we played the latest-- the latest popular music, you know, just from-- by ear.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was really pleasant.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I would say the entertainment that the children had at that time were so different from today, because I remember that we all went to other people's houses, and we played music.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, my parents insisted that every child had to practice half an hour, at least half an hour, a day.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- so when we came home from school, there was music in the house all the time for piano, violin, and then the cello.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I took pleasure in playing but not in practicing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was somehow an-- an ordeal to go and play always the same thing and go over it and-- but naturally, today, I'm very happy, very glad, that I was, to a certain extent, forced to practice.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I went to school first to-- to a Volksschule, which was at the-- at the age up to 10 years of age, I think, 10 or 11, which was in [NON-ENGLISH] in Vienna, which was in the 2nd District.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The district where we lived was the 2nd District, but it was a Jewish district.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A lot of Jews lived there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It wasn't a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, it was mixed people, but a lot of Jews lived there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember my first experience of antisemitism was in the Volksschule, in that-- in that young school, when-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when one of the other children from-- from a one class higher, maybe a year older than me, called me [NON-ENGLISH], you're a pig Jew.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I just run away.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
